Subject: [PATCH 06/15] ti_config_fragments/connectivity.cfg: enable keystone
 netcp cpts support

Enable support of cpts for both gbe and 10gbe on keystone
devices.

Signed-off-by: WingMan Kwok <w-kwok2@ti.com>
---
 ti_config_fragments/connectivity.cfg | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/ti_config_fragments/connectivity.cfg b/ti_config_fragments/connectivity.cfg
index 35e7375..926297f 100644
--- a/ti_config_fragments/connectivity.cfg
+++ b/ti_config_fragments/connectivity.cfg
@@ -138,6 +138,7 @@ CONFIG_NET_CLS_IND=y
 CONFIG_NET_SCH_FIFO=y
 CONFIG_IP_SCTP=m
 CONFIG_VLAN_8021Q=m
+CONFIG_TI_KEYSTONE_NETCP_CPTS=y
 
 #MDIO phys
 CONFIG_MICREL_PHY=y
